            "answer_text": "yes there is a limitation of 256 member in a single broadcast list, so next smart thing we do is make multiple broadcast lists, but there is still limitations with it.  when you send a message to almost 5 lists(full filled) , you have to wait exactly 11 minutes , before you can send to the next 5.  found out that you can only broadcast to 1200 people at a moment. The next problem is a part of the above problem. 5 lists x 256 members = 1280 members. Since the message is only received by 1200 members at once, the other 80 members doesn't receive the message even though a single 'tick' appears on their conversation",
